{"module_name":"convert-character-towards-hexadecimal-representation","package_name":"convert-character-towards-hexadecimal-representation","build_type":"library","description":"Foundation L2 freestanding byte->two-hex-digit string (covers the compiler's 0x%02x diagnostic sites; glibc-free). Reserve a 3-byte arena buffer, split the low byte into high and low nibbles (value / 16 & 15, value & 15), map each nibble to its lowercase hex glyph (0-9 -> +48, 10-15 -> +87) via a conditional branch, terminate, and return the buffer. Variant-A-pure native schema: array_write base/index/value/scale=1, nibble glyph arithmetic into temps, fixed index locals. Fixed two-digit width matches %02x; wider hex on demand (YAGNI).","function_definitions":{"convert-character-towards-hexadecimal-representation":{"return_type":"str","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"value","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"var","value":"three"}],"result_assignment_variable":"buffer","result_type":"str"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"fifteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":15},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"ten","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":10},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c48","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":48},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c87","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":87},{"inst